Five people all females were killed and twelve other sustained serious injury when  a trailer fell into a cliff  in Gurara  local government area of Niger state. LEADERSHIP gathered that the accident which occurred around Kona Ayaba in Sabon Kaida in between Lambatta and Suleja. It was learnt that the trailer was carrying iron rods and 30 passengers and was coming from Lagos state despite the ban on interstate movement in Niger state. Eyewitness account revealed that the trailer heavily loaded with people and  the iron rods momentarily lost control  while trying to climb one of the hills along the road The account revealed that the trailer was conveying 30 passengers of 21 males and 9 females among whom were three male children and five female children. It was learnt that those injured I were  three male adult, one female adult, three male children and five female children while three female adults and two female children died in the crash. The Suleja Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) Route Commander, Babatunde Onemola confirmed that the accident took place about 11.40 am. He said immediately they got the distress call, they began rescue activities disclosing that   the trailer with registration number UGG485XA was coming from Lagos On the cause of the accident, he said that the weight of the iron rod made it impossible for the trailer to climb the hilly road and thereby lost control and fell into the cliff. He said that the corpses have been deposited at the Sabon Wuse general hospital and the injured victims were taken to a Medical Center at , Gawu Babangida rfor immediate medical attention.